Thank You Gallery is proud to present ‘Foreign Shipment’ featuring work from legendary Jamaican sign painter Nurse.

Nurse Signs is the creation of Cleark “Nurse” James, Jamaican sign painter of over 35 years, whose distinct handstyle can be seen throughout Western Jamaica touting everything from Sunday Church services to strip clubs, soccer tournaments, bingo nights, fish frys, and most notably, the area’s nonstop itinerary of Dancehall parties. Beloved and respected within his Westmoreland Parish community (Nurse coaches over 100 kids in his role within the Negril Football Club), Nurse’s lengthy, nightly sign painting sessions attract a wide-ranging mix of characters “passing through” for a loose cigarette, a shot of rum, or to simply “shoot the breeze” while Nurse churns out a prolific amount of brilliantly colored, hand-painted signs. Recently, Nurse Signs has collaborated with The Brooklyn Museum, John Legend, Smith Street Tattoo Parlor, Apple Music, Wray & Nephew Rum, and Richardson Magazine

We are happy to present this collection of Nurse’s work featuring exclusive signs (imported directly from Jamaica) as well as collaborative items including a selection of curated handpainted custom signs and limited-edition Thank You Gallery x Nurse Merch.

This collection also showcases Nurse’s iconic sign shop & artwork via zines, prints, & the photography of Negril’s Christai Lynch & American artist, Matt Goias.

My friend. My brother. Nobody can believe you’re not here anymore. We all expected to see your smiling face forever. Maybe not as often as we used to, but none of us actually believes that you’re not just going to pop up, and everything will be like old times. Old times on the L train, in the club, at the diner at 5 am. Old times at Who’s Next? Old times in Paris, Japan, and Speeed (with three “e”s). I could go on and on. I’m so thankful for the recent times in my back yard. That’s the last time I saw you, and most of the old crew was there. We were side by side for so many amazing adventures. Some stories I will tell one day, and some of them I’ll have to smile and laugh to myself about. That’s just fine. I have enough wonderful memories of you to last ten lifetimes. You were the most universally loved person that I’ve ever met. Everywhere we went, we left with new friends, and an invitation to return. Because of you. We also often left with a bottle of champagne. I don’t remember you ever being angry or even too upset about anything. Ever. Even in situations where you absolutely had every right to be, you seemed to know that everything would work out - water would find it’s own level. That’s how I’m going to look at this. We don’t get to see you and talk and laugh and hug you anymore, but we will always remember you with nothing but love and respect. My brother. Our brother. You were the absolute best friend that a friend could be.

Please join us today (Wednesday) at 5 pm for our second staging of the @doublebarrelrumclub featuring a rum tasting with @hampdenestaterum. Based in the parish of Trelawny in the north west of Jamaica, Hampden Estate is one of the oldest sugar estates in Jamaica, and is the only distillery in Jamaica that specializes exclusively in the making of heavy pot still rums. Tasting begins promptly at 5 pm at the @misslilys Negril bar. Please join us for a journey through Jamaican rum!
